description:
As an API consumer
  I want to receive a confirmation that the API is alive
  So I can verify that the API is operational

elements.name: API responds successfully to a health check

steps.name: the API is available
a GET request is made to the Alive Endpoint
the API response should return a status code of 200
the Health Check response body should contain "Status" with the value "ALIVE-AND-KICKING"

name: API Health Check Endpoint

description:
As a user 
  I want to parse date tokens and receive the computed dates in the API response.
  So that the correct type of string is returned based on the input token in the API response.

steps.name: a valid or invalid date token "INVALIDTOKEN"
a GET request is made to the ParseDateToken Endpoint
the API response for the ParseDateToken Endpoint should return a status code of 400
the response body should contain "Error" with the value "Invalid string token format"
a valid or invalid date token "[TODAY]"
a GET request is made to the ParseDateToken Endpoint
the API response for the ParseDateToken Endpoint should return a status code of 200
the response body should contain "ParsedToken" with the value "today"
a valid or invalid date token "[TODAY-1YEAR-1MONTH]"
a GET request is made to the ParseDateToken Endpoint
the API response for the ParseDateToken Endpoint should return a status code of 200
the response body should contain "ParsedToken" with the value "one year and one month ago from today"
a valid or invalid date token "[TODAY+1YEAR-2MONTH]"
a GET request is made to the ParseDateToken Endpoint
the API response for the ParseDateToken Endpoint should return a status code of 200
the response body should contain "ParsedToken" with the value "one year ahead and two months ago from today"
a valid or invalid date token "[TOMORROW+3DAY]"
a GET request is made to the ParseDateToken Endpoint
the API response for the ParseDateToken Endpoint should return a status code of 200
the response body should contain "ParsedToken" with the value "tomorrow plus three days (four days from today)"
a valid or invalid date token "[YESTERDAY-2DAY]"
a GET request is made to the ParseDateToken Endpoint
the API response for the ParseDateToken Endpoint should return a status code of 200
the response body should contain "ParsedToken" with the value "yesterday minus two days (three days ago)"
a valid or invalid date token "[TODAY+2YEAR+6MONTH-15DAY]"
a GET request is made to the ParseDateToken Endpoint
the API response for the ParseDateToken Endpoint should return a status code of 200
the response body should contain "ParsedToken" with the value "two years and six months ahead of today minus 15 days"

name: Parse Date Token Endpoint

description:
As a user
    I want to parse tokens and generate strings based on different token formats
    So that the correct type of string is returned based on the input token in the API response.

steps.name: the ParseDynamicStringToken endpoint is running
A request with dynamic string token "INVALIDTOKEN" to the ParseDynamicStringToken endpoint
the API response should return a status code of 400 for the ParseDynamicStringToken endpoint
the response should contain "Error" with the value "Invalid string token format"
the ParseDynamicStringToken endpoint is running
A request with dynamic string token "[ALPHA-NUMERIC-5]" to the ParseDynamicStringToken endpoint
the API response should return a status code of 200 for the ParseDynamicStringToken endpoint
the response should contain "ParsedToken" with the value "An alpha-numeric string of length 5"
the ParseDynamicStringToken endpoint is running
A request with dynamic string token "[PUNCTUATION-3]" to the ParseDynamicStringToken endpoint
the API response should return a status code of 200 for the ParseDynamicStringToken endpoint
the response should contain "ParsedToken" with the value "A string of punctuation characters of length 3"
the ParseDynamicStringToken endpoint is running
A request with dynamic string token "[ALPHA-NUMERIC-PUNCTUATION-10-LINES-2]" to the ParseDynamicStringToken endpoint
the API response should return a status code of 200 for the ParseDynamicStringToken endpoint
the response should contain "ParsedToken" with the value "2 lines of strings with each line containing 10 alpha-numeric-punctuation characters"
the ParseDynamicStringToken endpoint is running
A request with dynamic string token "[NUMERIC-8]" to the ParseDynamicStringToken endpoint
the API response should return a status code of 200 for the ParseDynamicStringToken endpoint
the response should contain "ParsedToken" with the value "A numeric string of length 8"
the ParseDynamicStringToken endpoint is running
A request with dynamic string token "[SPECIAL-5-LINES-3]" to the ParseDynamicStringToken endpoint
the API response should return a status code of 200 for the ParseDynamicStringToken endpoint
the response should contain "ParsedToken" with the value "3 lines of strings with each line containing 5 special characters"
the ParseDynamicStringToken endpoint is running
A request with dynamic string token "[ALPHA-NUMERIC-SPECIAL-12]" to the ParseDynamicStringToken endpoint
the API response should return a status code of 200 for the ParseDynamicStringToken endpoint
the response should contain "ParsedToken" with the value "A mixed alpha, numeric, and special character string of length 12"

name: TokenDynamicStringParser String Generation

description:
In order to accurately compute dates from token format strings
    As a user of the TokenDateParser class
    I want to be able to input a variety of token strings and get the correct date output

steps.name: A date token "[TODAY]"
I parse the token
the result should equal today plus 0 years 0 months 0 days
A date token "[TOMORROW]"
I parse the token
the result should equal today plus 0 years 0 months 1 days
A date token "[YESTERDAY]"
I parse the token
the result should equal today plus 0 years 0 months -1 days
A date token "[TODAY-2YEAR-4MONTH]"
I parse the token
the result should equal today plus -2 years -4 months 0 days
A date token "[TODAY-1YEAR-1MONTH]"
I parse the token
the result should equal today plus -1 years -1 months 0 days
A date token "[TODAY-1YEAR-2MONTH-3DAY]"
I parse the token
the result should equal today plus -1 years -2 months -3 days
A date token "[TODAY+1YEAR-1MONTH+1DAY]"
I parse the token
the result should equal today plus 1 years -1 months 1 days
A date token "[TODAY+2YEAR]"
I parse the token
the result should equal today plus 2 years 0 months 0 days
A date token "[TODAY+5MONTH]"
I parse the token
the result should equal today plus 0 years 5 months 0 days
A date token "[TOMORROW+5MONTH]"
I parse the token
the result should equal today plus 0 years 5 months 1 days
A date token "[YESTERDAY+5MONTH-1YEAR]"
I parse the token
the result should equal today plus -1 years 5 months -1 days
